!! !!Analysis symbols
! ----------------

!! The morphological analyses of Somali wordforms are presented
!! in this system in terms of the following symbols.
!! (It is highly suggested to follow existing standards when adding new tags).

!! The parts-of-speech are:
 +N +V +A +Adp +Q +Pr +Adv +CC +CS +Interj +Pron +Num !!= * @CODE@

! TODO: copied this over, but need to remember why it was there.


!! Fusional adpositions

 +Adp/u	   !!= * @CODE@
 +Adp/ka   !!= * @CODE@
 +Adp/la   !!= * @CODE@
 +Adp/ku   !!= * @CODE@

!! Focus

+Foc/L +Foc/R  !!= * @CODE@

!! The parts of speech are further split up into:
 +Interr +Interr/ma +Attr +Short +Cmp     !!= * @CODE@
 +Der/sho +Pfx +PP +Sep +Com		      !!= * @CODE@
 +Appos +Impers +Inch				      !!= * @CODE@

 +Recit +Restr						      !!= * @CODE@

 +Pers								      !!= * @CODE@
 +Dem								      !!= * @CODE@
 +Coll								      !!= * @CODE@
 +Mass								      !!= * @CODE@
 +Acr								      !!= * @CODE@
 +Abstr								      !!= * @CODE@


!! Verb and noun declensions for the analysers that want to know about that

 +Decl/1 				      !!= * @CODE@
 +Decl/2 +Decl/2A +Decl/2B    !!= * @CODE@
 +Decl/3 +Decl/3A +Decl/3B    !!= * @CODE@
 +Decl/4 				      !!= * @CODE@
 +Decl/5				      !!= * @CODE@
 +Decl/6 				      !!= * @CODE@
 +Decl/7				      !!= * @CODE@

!! The Usage extents are marked using the following tags:

 +Use/Sub   
