!! !!!The continuation lexica

LEXICON Root   !!= * @CODE@ 

!! The word forms in Somali start from the lexeme roots of basic
!! word classes, or optionally from prefixes:

Abbreviations   ;   !!= * @CODE@

Nouns           ;   !!= * @CODE@
Numerals        ;   !!= * @CODE@

Pronouns        ;   !!= * @CODE@

Verbs           ;   !!= * @CODE@
Adjectives      ;   !!= * @CODE@

Adverbs         ;   !!= * @CODE@

Conjunctions    ;   !!= * @CODE@
Subjunctions    ;   !!= * @CODE@

Postpositions   ;   !!= * @CODE@
Determiners     ;   !!= * @CODE@
Interjections   ;   !!= * @CODE@
Punctuation     ;   !!= * @CODE@

!! !!The following are coming from som-lex.txt
!! * IrregularNounMorph ; 
!! * VerbalPrefixes ;	    
!! * IrregularAdjective ; 
!! * Adverb ;			    
!! * Prefixes  ;		    

LEXICON FINAL_NG !!= * @CODE@ just adds the +Use/NG tag to lower ##
 +Use/NG:{##} 	# ;

LEXICON FINAL !!= * @CODE@ just adds lower ##
 :{##} 	# ;

